Alstom, Carrefour, Casino, Perenco, Poweo: French Equity Preview

-- B y   A l a n   K a t z
-- 
2011-07-04T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/alstom-carrefour-casino-perenco-poweo-french-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose stocks may have unusual price changes in Paris. Symbols
are in parentheses after company names and prices are from the
last close.  France’s  CAC 40 Index (CAC)  rose 25.14 points, or 0.6 percent, to
4,007.35. The broader SBF 120 index gained 0.6 percent to
3,019.48.  Alstom SA (ALO)  : The world’s third-largest power-
equipment maker said it expects sales to rise in the second half
of the fiscal year ending March 2012, after orders began to
increase this year, the French weekly Investir reported, citing
Chief Executive Officer Patrick Kron. The shares fell 0.4
percent to 42.35 euros.  Carrefour SA (CA)  : The world’s second-largest retailer
purchased 100 percent of the shares in its Dia unit for 2.4
billion euros ($3.5 billion), or 3.50 euros a share, from its
fully owned subsidiary Norfin Holder S.L. The purchase price
will be adjusted in accordance with the opening price of Dia
shares on their first day of trading on the Madrid Stock
Exchange July 5. Carrefour shares fell 0.6 percent to 28.16
euros.  Casino Guichard-Perrachon SA (CO)  :   Brazil ’s development
bank may pull up to $2.9 billion of funds for Cia. Brasileira de
Distribuicao Grupo Pao de Acucar’s merger with Carrefour SA’s
local assets after Casino Guichard-Perrachon SA called the plan
illegal. BNDES, as the  state bank  is known, said its
participation in the proposed merger depends on a “friendly
understanding” among all involved. Casino shares rose 0.9
percent to 65.56 euros.  Perenco SA (226210Z FP): The French oil company’s Brazil
unit, Perenco Petroleo & Gas do Brasil Participacoes SA,
suspended its planned initial public offering for up to 60 days
because of the “current market situation,” according to a
statement posted on the company’s website.  Poweo (ALPWO)  SA: Verbund AG, Austria’s biggest utility,
said it’s in talks with potential buyers of its 46 percent stake
in the French company. Poweo shares rose 5.8 percent to 5.99
euros.  ST Dupont SA (DPT)  : The luxury-goods maker reported net
income of 3.5 million euros for the year ended March 31,
compared with an 8.8 million-euro loss a year earlier. Fourth-
quarter revenue rose 23 percent to 15.7 million euros. The
shares fell 1.4 percent to 71 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
